Technical director, Nigeria Football Federation, NFF, Augustine Eguavoen, has sent his best wishes to the Flying Eagles ahead of the 2023 Africa U-20 Cup of Nations. The biennial competition will kick-off on Sunday. The Flying Eagles will be in action on the opening day against the Junior Terangha Lions of Senegal. The game at the Cairo International Stadium will start at 6pm Nigerian time. Eguavoen, a former Super Eagles head coach, has tasked the team to do well in the competition. “All the best to the Flying Eagles as they head out for the U20 AFCON in Egypt,” he wrote on his Twitter handle.